notes: Data for regions (including TAs) has been derived from a mix of student-related indicators such as secondary school location, postcode of student's term or permanent address, and provider delivery site. Numbers should be taken as indicative only.
Levels of study refer to ‘qualification types’ as set out in the New Zealand Qualifications Framework. Levels are based on complexity, with level 1 the least complex and level 10 the most complex.
